title.narrative: PEACEBUILDING AND SURVIVE AND THRIVE- PROTECTION FROM CONFLICT AND DISASTERS

description.narrative: Strengthened capacities of health authorities and local government units to scale up quality maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health, nutrition, water and sanitation services and information in BARMM, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Sanitation, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, more children, adolescents and women, particularly the most vulnerable, benefit from improved and equitable neonatal, child, maternal and adolescent health and nutrition services, and adopt healthy life practices.

description.narrative: High coverage of community-based nutrition and vaccination services was maintained at 84% and 87% respectively in municipalities for which data is available, after near doubling of coverage in 2018. Three additional municipalities in Maguindanao Province were declared open defecation free, making 10 municipalities OD-free to date, out of the 118 total municipalities and two cities in the Autonomous Region. Basic capacities and government commitments are now in place to expand nutrition, immunization and sanitation programming on a wider scale in 2020. Progress was constrained by the outbreak of polio and Mindanao earthquakes in the second half of the year. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/02/2020
